                },
                {
                    "text": " under the sink was slowly damaging the cabinet"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Common housing complaint. 'Leaky' describes anything allowing liquid/gas to escape unintentionally (leaky roof, leaky faucet)."
        },
        {
            "word": "dripping faucet",
            "wordType": "noun phrase",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "A tap that continues to release "
                },
                {
                    "text": "small drops of water",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " even when turned off, often due to a "
                },
                {
                    "text": "worn washer",
                    "highlight2": true
                }
            ],
            "arabicMeaning": "صنبور يقطر",
            "synonyms": [
                "leaky tap",
                "dripping tap"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "The constant sound of the "
                },
                {
                    "text": "dripping faucet",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " kept me awake all night in the hotel room"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Wastes water and increases bills. Easy DIY fix usually involves replacing the rubber washer inside the faucet handle."
        },
        {
            "word": "cracked windshield",
            "wordType": "noun phrase",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "The front window of a vehicle that has "
                },
                {
                    "text": "broken lines or splits",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " in the glass without "
