            "tips": "Stronger than 'dirty'—implies unacceptable, offensive dirtiness. Common complaint word for rentals, restaurants, and public facilities."
        },
        {
            "word": "worn",
            "wordType": "adjective",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "Damaged or "
                },
                {
                    "text": "thinned by repeated use",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " over time; showing "
                },
                {
                    "text": "signs of age and deterioration",
                    "highlight2": true
                }
            ],
            "arabicMeaning": "بالٍ / مستهلك",
            "synonyms": [
                "worn-out",
                "frayed",
                "deteriorated"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "The carpet in the hallway was completely "
                },
                {
                    "text": "worn",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " down to the backing after ten years of heavy foot traffic"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Often used for tires ('worn tread' = dangerous), shoes, carpets, and clothing. 'Worn out' = completely unusable from overuse."
        },
        {
            "word": "warranty",
            "wordType": "noun",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "A written "
                },
                {
                    "text": "guarantee from a manufacturer",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " promising to repair or replace a product if it "
                },
                {
                    "text": "fails within a specific time",
                    "highlight2": true
                }
            ],
            "arabicMeaning": "ضمان",
            "synonyms": [
                "guarantee",
                "service agreement"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "The laptop stopped working after eight months, but thankfully it was still under "
                },
                {
                    "text": "warranty",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " so the company replaced it for free"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Always keep warranty documents and receipts. 'Full warranty' covers everything; 'limited warranty' has exclusions. Voided by misuse or unauthorized repairs."
        },
        {
            "word": "I'd rather",
            "wordType": "phrase",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "Short for 'I would rather'; used to state a "
                },
                {
                    "text": "clear preference",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " when making a "
                },
                {
                    "text": "complaint or negotiation",
                    "highlight2": true
                }
            ],
            "arabicMeaning": "أفضل أن...",
            "synonyms": [
                "I would prefer",
                "I'd prefer to"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "\"We can fix the tear or give you store credit.\" \""
                },
                {
                    "text": "I'd rather",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " have a full refund, please.\""
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Polite but firm way to state your preferred solution during complaints. Followed by base verb: 'I'd rather have...' NOT 'I'd rather to have...'"
        },
        {
            "word": "have it repaired",
            "wordType": "causative phrase",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "To arrange for someone else to fix something for you; using the "
                },
                {
                    "text": "causative structure",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " 'have + object + past participle' to show you "
                },
                {
                    "text": "cause an action to happen",
                    "highlight2": true
                }
            ],
            "arabicMeaning": "أصلحه (باستخدام الغير)",
            "synonyms": [
                "get it fixed",
                "arrange for repairs"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "My washing machine broke yesterday, so I'm going to "
                },
                {
                    "text": "have it repaired",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " by a professional technician tomorrow"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Key complaint language pattern: 'have it checked/replaced/returned'. Shows you're taking action rather than doing the repair yourself."
        },
        {
            "word": "no signal",
            "wordType": "phrase",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "Complete "
                },
                {
                    "text": "absence of reception",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " for phone calls, internet, or television in a particular "
                },
                {
                    "text": "location",
                    "highlight2": true
                }
            ],
            "arabicMeaning": "لا إشارة",
            "synonyms": [
                "no reception",
                "dead zone"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "I couldn't call for help when my car broke down because my phone showed "
                },
                {
                    "text": "no signal",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " in that remote valley"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Common electronics complaint. Different from 'weak signal' (some bars but poor quality). Buildings, mountains, and weather can block signals."
